# Activating {{ project_name }} with Claude Code and Cowork

This project was generated from the DATAVIDENCE template. Creating/renaming the
project is already done (via `copier copy`). This guide covers the **first run**:
how to inject context in Claude Code, generate the Cowork bridge, and start in
Cowork. Do **not** run `/init` — a curated `CLAUDE.md` already ships here.

## 1. First run in Claude Code — inject context from the start

`cd` into this folder and start `claude`. It auto-loads `CLAUDE.md` + `.claude/`.
Paste the **startup prompt** below as your first message. Fill the
`[ADDITIONAL_CONTEXT]` block with whatever describes this project (goal, data,
audience, constraints, deadlines). The prompt makes the agent read the rules
first and then adapt the *contextualizable* artifacts to your project.

```text
Read these files first, in this exact order, before doing anything else:
  1. .claude/constitution.md
  2. .claude/policies/00-index.md  (then the specific policy a task needs)
  3. .claude/knowledge-map.md
  4. CLAUDE.md  (note the overlay table)
  5. PROJECT_BRIEF.md

Project context to apply:
[ADDITIONAL_CONTEXT]
<!-- Paste here: what this project is, goals, constraints, data sources,
     audience, success criteria, deadlines, out-of-scope. -->

Then, using only that context and what is in this repo:
- Adapt the CONTEXTUALIZABLE artifacts to this project, and PROPOSE the diffs
  (apply only after I confirm):
    • PROJECT_BRIEF.md  — goal, constraints, glossary, success criteria, out-of-scope
    • CLAUDE.md overlay — map each generic gate to this project's real command
    • .claude/knowledge-map.md — add rows for this project's own documents
- Do NOT invent facts, data, or citations. If it is not in the context or the
  repo, say "unknown" and ask me.
- Mark uncertainty explicitly; separate fact / inference / hypothesis / recommendation.
- Ask before any irreversible or outward-facing action.
- Write all outputs under outputs/.
- Do NOT run /init.
```

The ORTHOGONAL layer (constitution, policies, hooks, the plugin, hygiene, CI) is
identical across projects and is **not** edited per project — only the
contextualizable artifacts above change.

## 2. Install the companion plugin (one-time, machine-global)

Guardrails (skills, hooks, subagents) come from the `psotobverse-utils` plugin,
not from this repo. In Claude Code:

```text
/plugin marketplace add psotob91/psotobverse-utils
/plugin install psotobverse-utils@psotobverse-utils
```

## 3. Generate the Cowork bridge (right after Code setup)

Cowork does **not** auto-read `CLAUDE.md`/`.claude/`. In a Code session, run:

```text
/psotobverse-utils:sync-cowork
```

It writes `.claude/COWORK_INSTRUCTIONS.md` (the constitution + read-order +
overlay as a paste block) and prints its path. Claude will ask you to **approve**
the write (`.claude/` files are treated as sensitive) — approve it. Then open that
file and copy the `[PASTE FROM HERE] … [END]` block.

## 4. First time in Cowork (GUI — there is no Cowork CLI)

1. Claude Desktop → **Cowork → Customize → Plugins** → add marketplace
   `psotob91/psotobverse-utils` and install **psotobverse-utils** (once per machine).
2. **Cowork → Projects → + → Use an existing folder** → select this project's folder.
3. Paste `.claude/COWORK_INSTRUCTIONS.md` into the project **Instructions** field.
4. Add the `context/` folder as the project **Context**.
5. Run the one-time **`docs/cowork-verification-checklist.md`** to confirm the
   plugin's hooks fire and `$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR` resolves in Cowork.

Re-run `/psotobverse-utils:sync-cowork` whenever the constitution or policies change, and re-paste.
